The result of the first election was regarded with surprise in some quarters and one local newspaper predicted that would be successful in the by-election.<ref>{{cite news|title=District Notes|url=http://welshnewspapers.llgc.org.uk/en/page/view/3027599/ART37|accessdate=7 January 2014|newspaper=Aberdare Times|date=9 February 1889}}</ref> He was, however, defeated by Thomas Davies of [[Abercwmboi]].<ref>{{cite news|title=County Council Election|url=http://welshnewspapers.llgc.org.uk/en/page/view/3027609/ART37|accessdate=7 January 2014|newspaper=Aberdare Times|date=23 February 1889}}</ref>

