Davies was again re-elected in [[1895 Glamorgan County Council election|1895]]. He was opposed by Thomas Rees, landlord of the Swan Hotel, Aberaman and elected a member of the [[Aberdare Urban District Council]] at the inaugural [[1894 Aberdare Urban District Council election|1894]] election. The Merthyr Times opined that there was no necessity for a contest, and that the unsuccessful candidate had wasted his time and money.<ref name="MT 7-3-95 CC elections">{{cite news|title=County Council Elections|url=http://welshnewspapers.llgc.org.uk/en/page/view/3098680/ART21|accessdate=30 April 2014|newspaper=Merthyr Times|date=7 March 1895}}</ref> 
